President Trump delivered remarks in the East Room of the White House celebrating the six-month anniversary of the tax cuts and reforms that were signed into law. He highlighted the positive impact of the tax cuts, such as job creation, higher wages, and increased investment in the country. The President also mentioned the recent shooting at the Capital Gazette newsroom in Annapolis, Maryland, expressing condolences to the victims' families and vowing to reduce violent crime. He concluded his speech by emphasizing the importance of fair trade and the revival of American industries.